conversation_turns.message: My amh 0.68 afc 4 age 34+.doctor advised for donor egg. Should I go with donor egg or self egg
I understand your situation... We have seen that fresh eggs have slightly higher success rates but are more expensive, while frozen eggs offer more flexibility and lower costs...
In my case donor option is have better chance.?

Given your low AMH (0.68) and AFC (4), along with your age, the donor egg option typically offers significantly higher success rates compared to using your own eggs. Our frozen egg bank guarantees mature, high-quality eggs which bypasses the issue of your own ovarian reserve.
